node.text:
Do you know what I think is cool….

Seeing women OWN who they are. Proudly embrace their body at all stages. Wear the damn shorts, rock that bikini, wear their favourite sports bra….even if not at their leanest.

Seeing ladies upping their calories to maintenance and above. Breaking free of constantly living in a calorie deficit and the extreme dieting mindset.

Seeing all my bad aass girls lifting weights & having strength goals. There is something so empowering about saying goodbye to endless hours of cardio & focusing on lifting weights and getting stronger. Exercise should not be purely to burn calories or to look ‘thin’.

Seeing women building empires & chasing career goals.

Seeing women supporting each other instead of tearing each other down. Her win does not mean your loss. Cheer loud for that girl next to you...even if she is pretty, even if she is smart, even if she is successful, even if you aren’t happy with where you are at right now...because one day you will really need that applause too.

I love this quote:

‘A glowing woman can help other women glow and still be lit.’ 👑✨

FIX YOUR FORM: GOBLET SQUAT ❌✅

SAVE + RESHARE! 🙏🏼

Goblet squats have been a staple in my programs lately, especially when working out from home. To make them extra savage you can add a long restiance band around you) 
It’s also a great exercise for beginners to train the squat movement pattern.

Weight is in front making it easier to keep your torso upright and for balance.

💡I am doing it with a heel elevation to help with ankle mobility which allows you to sit deeper and also makes it easier for your knees to travel forward.

❌Common mistakes:
Weight is held too far forward away from chest
Leaning torso forward
Weight held too low
Core not engaged

✅Good form cues:
Weight is held close to chest
Maintain a neutral spine
Torso upright
Knees track out in line with toes
Core braced

I hope this was helpful. Let me know what other HOME exercises you would like a breakdown on! 🙏🏼

@laurensimpsonfitness

node.text:
ARE YOU LOCKING OUT YOUR HIP THRUSTS? 🤔🍑🍑 SWIPE!

Girls, don’t miss out on getting those glute gains - make sure you are reaching full hip extension when you are doing your hip thrusts!

When the weight is too heavy often people fall short of locking it out at the top...you can get it off the ground but fall short of being able to push your hips up to full extension. It is the top range where your glutes are under the most amount of tension. 🔥🔥

So if you are failing to hit this, you aren’t maximising your glute engagement (and you might not actually feel hip thrusts in your glutes how you should).

There is nothing wrong with dropping the weight so you can focus on your form. Lift with intent and to engage the correct muscles - don’t just lift for your ego or to just get the exercise over and done with quickest. 😅

To help with your hip extension lockout you can focus on paused hip thrusts or Kas glute bridge which do focus on maximising that top range and get you familiar with this range of motion. 🔥🔥🔥

🖤Paused hip thrust: Isomeric hold at the top for 3 seconds. Squeeze glutes and focus on keeping your positioning at the full lockout. The big pause allows you to spend more time where glutes are contracted.

🖤Kas glute bridge
Shorter range of motion where you are working the top range only. Controlled reps with the intent of shortening your glutes.

I hope this video is helpful.
@laurensimpsonfitness

How to improve your relationship with your body? ✨

🧚🏻‍♀️Conquer your inner mean girl. Stop making negative comments about your body. If you wouldn’t say it to your bestie, your mum or your daughter - why do you say it about yourself? Hating your body is not the solution.

🧚🏻‍♀️Stop with the all or nothing mindset. If you have an off day or feeling not great - it’s not a reason to completely give up on yourself. Loving your body and having a good relationship with food and training is something you want to sustain long term - it’s not a short term fix.

🧚🏻‍♀️Stop obsessing over the number on the scale. If this triggers you - seriously throw the scale out. I have never owned a scale. This number DOES NOT and SHOULD NOT dictate your self worth.

🧚🏻‍♀️Stop comparing yourself to other women! YOU are YOU. This is so powerful.

Being confident in your body takes time & is something that constantly needs work on.

So go own that beautiful bod you have been blessed with 💕🌈

node.text:
GLUTES @ HOME 🍑🔥 using a long band (ft a curious Rocky) 🐺

Please hit SAVE + let me know if this post was helpful! ❤️

I love using long bands with home training as it does provide extra resistance and also can mimic the cable machine.

🔥HIP BANDED DB ROMANIAN DEADLIFT

-Band set at hip height
-Torso on a slight lean with tension against band
-DB path is further away from the body in comparison to a typical RDL
-Long band provides resistance throughout the exercise
🍑Bottom range of RDL = glutes in the lengthened position
🍑Top range of the RDL with edition of band = glutes in the shortened position.

🔥BANDED HIP EXTENSION @coach_kassem 

-Single leg exercise
-Resistance band is on the non working leg
-Maintain slight bend in knee as you hinge back and then drive hips forward into full extension.
-Holding onto something for stability

🔥STRAIGHT LEG ABDUCTION

- I have attached my ankle strap to the long band.
- This one will hit your GLUTE MINIMUS - it is a small muscle and assists with hip abduction.
- Bring your leg out straight to the side.

🔥KICKBACK

- Using the ankle strap attachment again.
- Target your glute max in the shortened position.
- Glutes are at a peak contraction at the top range.

‘NEVER MISS TWICE’

Let’s be honest. There are times we slip up, we make mistakes, we fall off track, we have off days. It’s reality…we are only human! The key is not to give up.

My rule as inspired by James Clear in the book ‘Atomic Habits’ is NEVER MISS TWICE. (*if you have not already read this book do yourself a favour and get it!*) 👏🏼

If you had a bad day with your diet, if you skipped a workout or if you had a day feeling ‘meh’…find a way to get back on track as soon as you can.

Don’t let those bad habits and behaviours snowball. Break that chain.⛓

Mistakes and slip ups are all part of the process - but they shouldn’t become part of the pattern.✔️

Heading into a new week I want you to remember this rule. Ditch the all or nothing approach.

You got this ✌🏼

Outfit: @rarecollective_official 
I’m wearing size small 🧡🔥

Adding weight to your back extensions 🔥🔥🔥💥

PLEASE SAVE + RESHARE IF ITS HELPFUL ❤️

Here are some different ways you can add weight to your back extensions. Typically, the closer the weight is to your centre of mass - the easier it’s going to be. For example - holding it close in to your chest is going to be easier than both the prisoner style and then holding the plate up at head height away from your body.

The moment arm changes with each of these variations. Moment arm refers to the distance between your hip joint and the load.

💡You can do this as a ‘mechanical drop set’….start with reps of the hardest variations which is weight at head height, then bring the plate to behind your head, then to your chest.

➡️Weight at your chest: 
Holding the weight in close to your chest reduces the moment arm.
The distance is smaller that the load needs to travel.

➡️Weight held behind head:
“Prisoner” position
I got this from @coach__carroll 
Increases the moment arm as the weight is now further away from your centre of mass compared to when at chest.

➡️Weight held out away from body at head height:
This is the hardest variation as the weight is further away from your centre of mass.
Moment arm is increased again.
There is also increased tension on your glutes as more power is needed to complete your reps.
Your core needs to be engaged also.

I hope this was helpful! ❤️
@laurensimpsonfitness

node.text:
Lockdown life + body update 🔒

Every Sunday I’m going to post a little life update.🙋🏼‍♀️

Here in Sydney we have just finished our 9th week in lockdown. 🥺 If you saw my stories yesterday I had a bit of a ‘meh’ feeling day. The reality of lockdown usually hits most on weekends. Feeling lethargic, unmotivated and a little deflated is totally human in these circumstances. I’m usually a ball of positivity but sometimes I do think it’s equally important to be REAL about it too. ✨

Also just last night Mark and I got some exciting news which we will share soon! 🥳
(No I’m not pregnant lol)

NUTRITION + TRAINING INFO: 📝

🎯Goal: Calorie deficit = fat loss phase coming into Summer in Australia & give me a focus during lockdown.

⚖️Weight: Not sure as I don’t own scales.

🍪 Calories: 1650 calories each day + 1 untracked meal per week. I had a bit of an off weekend (I’m not 100% perfect all the time) but todays a new day!

🏋🏼‍♀️ Training: I am doing the @laurensimpsonfitness 8 week Challenge ‘Advanced’ HOME program option. This week has been the BEST training I’ve done in a while. LSF workouts are 🔥

🥊I’ve also just started boxing with @dillongauci . I’ll be doing boxing once per week!

👟Steps: 12,000 per day. My coastal walks in the morning have become part of my iso-routine daily. Good for the soul 😇

😴I average around 5-6 hours sleep per night. I’ve been feeling a little stressed, overwhelmed and have a super active mind. Working on this. 

❤️
Your reminder:
CONTROL WHAT YOU CAN.
BE A KIND HUMAN.

Sending my love and strength to everyone ✨Loz xoxo
